    "## Maturity Ratings\n",
    "\n",
    "A content rating rates the suitability of programs to inform the targeted audience in making an objective decision.Understanding the content ratings system:\n",
    "\n",
    "**The Motion Picture Association (MPAA) film rating system**\n",
    "\n",
    "    G – General Audiences: All ages admitted. Nothing that would offend parents for viewing by children.\n",
    "    \n",
    "    PG – Parental Guidance Suggested: Some material may not be suitable for children. Parents urged to give “parental guidance”. May contain some   material parents might not like for their young children.\n",
    "    \n",
    "    PG-13 – Parents Strongly Cautioned: Some material may be inappropriate for children under 13. Parents are urged to be cautious. Some material may be inappropriate for pre-teenagers.\n",
    "    \n",
    "    R – Restricted: Under 17 requires accompanying parent of adult guardian. Contains some adult material. Parents are urged to learn more about the film before taking their young children with them.\n",
    "    \n",
    "    NC-17 – Adults Only: No one 17 and under admitted. Clearly adult. Children are not admitted.\n",
    "\n",
    "**The TV Parental Guidelines**\n",
    "\n",
    "    TV-Y: Program is designed to be appropriate for all children. Thematic elements portrayed are specifically designed for a very young audience.\n",
    "    \n",
    "    TV-Y7: Program is designed for children age 7 and above. Thematic elements portrayed contain mild fantasy and comedic violence.\n",
    "    \n",
    "    TV-G: Program is generally suitable for all audiences. Thematic elements portrayed contain little or no violence, mild language, and little or no sexual dialogue or situations.\n",
    "    \n",
    "    TV-PG: Program contain some materials parents or guardians may find inappropriate for younger children. Thematic elements may include infrequent coarse language, some sexual content, some suggestive dialogue, or moderate violence.\n",
    "    \n",
    "    TV-14: Program contain materials that parents or guardians may find unsuitable for children under the age of 14. Thematic elements contain intensely suggestive dialogue, strong coarse language, intense sexual situations or intense violence.\n",
    "    \n",
    "    TV-MA: Program contains content that may be unsuitable for children. Thematic elements may include crude indecent language, explicit sexual activity and graphic violence.\n",
    "\n",
    "To achieve a cohesive report analysis the ratings system has been standardized during the cleaning and data validation processes. Notable changes include assigning the 16+ ratings within the Amazon Prime dataset to Young Adults due to varying ratings and online complaints of Amazon incorrectly assigning TV-MA contents to the rating. Additionally, leaving the 18+ ratings untouched due to the ambiguity of categorizing it to NC-17 or R without properly vetting each title.\n",
    "\n",
    "So, how are the content ratings of these streaming platforms distributed?"
   ]
