    "## Afterword\n",
    "\n",
    "The exploration led to a couple of insights and understanding of the four streaming services. For one, Netflix exhibited the highest percentage of matured rated content while Disney+ alternately lacked in that regard but hosted  content suitable for all audiences. Hulu had the largest unassigned content maturity rating and was also the closest to Disney+’s audience out of any of the explored service. Additionally, Hulu’s library ratio was the closest in the regards of almost equal content between TV Shows and Movies.\n",
    "\n",
    "The overall library of the streaming services leaned towards newer released content. The oldest titles found in the data set were on the Amazon Prime’s platform which included three drama movies released in 1920. As to the library trending towards newer released content, a possible future analysis could investigate the relationship between the rise of newer released content added to the platform and the streaming services producing their own digital content.\n",
